caption: Delicious! The best eggplant I've ever had!

My boyfriend and I often order from The Little India restaurant. Always a wonderful experience. Great food, reasonable prices and excellent customer service. They're located just next to the Bryn Mawr station so stopping in is really easy.

I am not recommended this place,I’m new On the area try to Order to pick send i do t see menu on the web  so I’m watching. The bad pic from  what the have  the person how answer. He not give me changes to say what. I wanna order. He hang up of me  so have bad actitud
Tasty food, speedy service. My go to when I'm in the neighborhood!
They serve large portions and for affordable pricing. kind employees. Will visit again.
TASTELESS food, I wouldn’t recommend this place to anyone. Quite expensive and tasteless food . Bad food

The worst Indian food in Chicago. I am Indian I eat Indian food at all the times , I am a tourist I travel places to place ,I like to try Indian food from every state or city I visit , but this was the worst and very expensive Indian food for a small dish. The goat curry was the worst and the naan was very thick and huge. This food has no taste . I don’t recommend this place at all . A BIG NO FOR THIS PALCE.
ATTENTION TOURISTS!!! if you’re looking For Indian food please don’t go here! food was horrible and disgusting! I would give 0 stars
Called for local delivery. Hot and tasty

#TBT Our first time experiencing Indian food was last year in October.  We were very fortunate to have our meal at the Little India Restaurant on Bryn Mawr.  We had the chef's special lunch which was $9 per person ( on weekdays) and there was a ton of delicious food.  There was way more than any of us could finish,  but, I happily took my leftovers home for the next day.  Such a great lunch and delicious meal for our introduction to Indian food!
Yummy

This restaurant I have been to in the past as well. I found it on yelp for the good reviews it has. The place is located in a shopping center. Parking is not so great but I was able to find a parking right in front. It was a Sunday evening and it was pretty packed. We got seated quickly. The lady was nice but she was in a real rush to get our order. The food was great. Tasted really good. Would come back again!
Ordered delivery for my first Indian food experience. Everything was delicious (Chana Masala, rice, and somosas) and it was affordable with huge portions!

Worst customer service ever. I went there to order food and ask for catering for friend party. She was treating me like I’m her servant. Plus she said it’s Covid and I don’t touch or put my stuff anywhere. I work with In prevention so after anyone leaves they should wipe it all. Or they close the place. People dine in restaurant nowadays. So that’s unacceptable. Customer service is number one in marketing. If you don’t know how to treat people then learn
Great place to relax, people watch, eat good food or all the above.  I had a cousin come into town and asked me to take him back here. Menu is similar to a restaurant in Jacksonville I loved.
this place is absolutely outstanding. the staff was friendly and sociable. i see why this place has a lot of great reviews.
Terrible! Completely ruined our order and then tried to charge us delivery to fix it. Very rude on the phone. Will never order from here again.
Great inclusive environment to all customers great vegan food me and my significant other will revist them soon

The flavors were okay but not enjoyed by everyone in our group. Ordered 4 entrees, 1 appetizer, and naan. Was very surprised when our order arrived with no rice! I called the restaurant to see if this was a mistake, it was not. I wish we would have known that when placing the order. Considering every other Indian food place I've ordered from in Chicago and beyond has come with a side of rice, they should make this more clear online.

I take my family to this lovely spot quite often! This is the best place to have a bite.  I go to this spot routinely. The food is very good, the team is professional and the rates are affordable. I enjoy meeting in this restaurant for a tasty meal.
Everything is delicious, especially the samosa chat and gobi manchurian. Order was ready quickly and Maria who took our order was thorough and helpful! We'll be back!
Good experience But it is costy litte bit

The only reason its not 5 stars is the price. The food quality is top shelf. The Josh Rogan is really flavorful, garlic naan is delightful. However, for $15 for a dish without rice and a lot of sauce (delicious sauce) is kinda silly.  28 June 2020 update - $2 extra charge just showed up on my statement days later, receipt long gone. Hope it was worth it, won't be back.

Haven’t dined in, but a pro is they deliver. I found it to be overpriced for the quality. Have had better Indian for less $. Found many dishes to be somewhat bland compared to other favorite Indian restaurants in Chicago.

Great sized portions. Affordable price. Clean establishment. Delivery was quack and professional!! and the Naan was probably the best I’ve ever had. Seriously the naan. Was so. Good. I can’t believe how good the naan was.
Chicken masala a must have. Get the Samosas...sweet sauce was fantastic. Will be coming back...my first of many future visits.
Nice Indian food. Not spicy.
My boyfriend and I got a food poisoning from a lunch buffet.
Great lunch specials and awesome weekend buffet.
Awesome and flavorful food, I like the vibes the spot has, and the employees were very friendly. I will surely come back in the future.

Yesterday was the first time in this magnificent restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last. We enjoyed the evening very much with the attentive service, with the high quality cooking and booze and with the honest cost. We will no doubt return there in a short time.
Great little restaurant.  Amazing authentic Indian food.  Everything was delicious.  We ate off the buffet; a plethora of exceptional dishes.
My favorite restaurant. Always fresh and delicious.
Great food! Wish the entrees came with rice like at most other Indian restaurants, but the taste is unbeatable. Definitely one of the best Indian food around.
I oder combo to go ..... food tastes like 2 days old
Super affordable. Especially since you get sooo much food!
Good food
Chicken makhani (butter chicken) was great. A little more sweet than most other places but the spice was just right.

This restaurant is solidly above average. While you won't be blown away by anything you get here, you also probably won't be disappointed. One thing that isn't advertised online is that there is an AYCE lunch buffet on the weekends.
Delicious food. Little small place as the name suggests...!!! Lady executive who took orders, did her job really very well....handled  customers with due respect and courtesy.

This place is very, very good. The sad thing is very few places on Devon are any good anymore. This place is in edgewater and has great authentic and spicy Indian food. The service is always wonderful and the food is delicious. The food here is good and spicy and really delicious. The buffet on sundays mornings is absolutely wonderful.
Good food and is consistent

I've enjoyed the food, which isn't as heavy as restaurant Indian often is, and above average for what I've had.  I don't visit more often because the room is rather glum, stale. From its aesthetics only, dinner at Little India is better suited for breaking up than foreplay.
Food was delicious, and tidy interior. Will definitely visit again. The food in the picture are Naan, plain rice, and chicken tikka masala

Authentic Indian cuisine at a very affordable price. The ingredients of their food is truly authentic and distinct. They serve buffets on weekends and this is a good way to taste their different dishes for one price. Don't expect too many choices but for the cheap price, it is worth it. I recommend their goat curry.
The service is great. Food isnt bad but certain dishes like the Rogan Josh can be avoided.
Very good food. The spicy dishes were spicy. The spices in the other dishes were very fragrant, maybe fresh ground?
Delicious food and excellent service! Get the keema!
Fantastic food and very friendly staff
Very nice taste and nice service
This is my favorite Indian restaurant in Chicago. The food is great, the atmosphere is fun, people are nice.
My favorite Indian in Chicago.
(Translated by Google) Excellent meal  (Original) Excelente comida
i give this place double thumbs up. really nothing but good experiences here. prices are fair.
this location is one of my favorites. the service here is great.
Very clean and warm services.

I have been coming here for years. Good makhani paneer, samosas, and mango lassi, but not outstanding. If you live in the area, this place is good enough, though it is a but pricey. The dine in area is pretty small, and they seem to do most of their business in takeouts. Staff is courteous.
the best indian food we have ever had.
Nice, simple and great food!
(Translated by Google) Too rich  (Original) Demasiado rico
Food is not good taste or quality. Staff behaviour is different for different nationals. They don't respect Indians. Not recommended place

A bit pricy, but Food is tasty and portions are sufficent Reastsurant always clean. Staff friendly. Three stars for twice failed customer service when order was inaccurate. First time I had to argue and insist the right order be delivered. It was not an automatic resolution with them. Tonight again I arrived home with my dinner to find the wrong order. Again they asked me to come back. No offer to deliver the correct order. So I trekked the 4 blocks back  again in 35 degr weather in the dark.  No apology and they actually took back the container of food I had eaten from. I purchased two  naans which would have been excellent customer service  had they said no charge for mistake and your inconvenience. but they did not.
Excellent authentic Indian food my 1st time there .I eat a lot of Indian food and they are actually very very good ! Great service! Excellent home made Chai
The best Indian food I have tasted ever
maria is awsome , good service and good quality food must come ..
The best palak paneer & dal makhni I've had. Food is spicy but good. Great garlic naan. Lovely family run local spot.
OMG!!!!! THEE Best
I love the fact that I have such good korma within walking distance from my house!
The taste of India in Chicago !

I tried tomato soup which was like hot tomato sauce. all kinds of vegetable appetizers here smell like reused oil. Veg and non veg entrees are just average. I like to have only samosa chat and bhel puri here. Once it was so annoying when the server was not accepting a mobile coupon saying his owner refuses to accept them unless we carry a printout. Why does someone carry a printout when the website provides and says mobile coupons accepted. The buffet here is just average. Who expects a indian buffet with no veg / non veg biryani. Also the server refused to give lemon and onion saying he wont serve anything from kitchen thats not on buffet.Rediculous behavior.
Tasty buffet!!
Good food. Reasonably priced. Bad parking, or rather no parking spots available at all.
Food is incredible! Awesome people that work there! Food is mind blowing good ! Will be back very soon
Beautiful happy veggie food (there's meat too I just didn't have it)
Brunch was really delicious
Food is great. Lunch prices are awesome. Solid 4.5 stars
Excellent food and service. Small dinning area and parking in the street. Fair prices good food good service. Cheap dinner since is a BYOB.
Great quality food. I always get the combos because you get much more variety that would be otherwise expensive to order as separate dishes.
The food there is reasonably priced and tastes better than any of the shops in Devon.
The weekend lunch buffet is amazing! For $11 you get to sample some of their best dishes! Authentic Indian cuisine!
Paneer Tikka Masala, Dal Makhani, Garlic Naan, Rice and Mango Lassi.

Wow! This place was really excellent! I came here on Saturday for the buffet. All of the food was astounding, and if you have room, there is even desert. Days it is not a buffet, there is a great variety of food, that comes really quick!

Ok, so let me start by saying that I intended to go to Devon Ave, but when I asked google gave me directions to "Little India" this is where it sent me, Lol.  That said, this was a really great place.  The food was delicious, portions were huge (my order of race and matter paneer fed two people), and the staff were so kind and polite.  Prices seemed reasonable.  Definitely recommend.
Get the lunch buffet.

I went to the weekend buffet and it was good.  So I ordered carry out chicken Vindaloo this eve.  It was the worst I've ever had and this is one of my favorite indian dishes.  Also, The $14 price for only 8oz was a bit stingy.  There are better choices for Indian food.

I really enjoy having the veggie combo here. I was told it could be made vegan and at another time that the naan was prepared with milk so I'd check with that if it's important to you. The food can be a bit oily in my opinion but nonetheless the food is great.
Been eating here since they opened in 2008. Buffet on weekends $12 person.Great food with lots vegetarian selections
Great variety-  excellent servings & service.
Love this place and the spicey tandoori chicken is spot on!

Great service and even better food!  Friend who was with me was delighted as she had been looking for a local Indian restaurant that tasted fresh and good and she announced she'd found it here.  She's been back multiple times since!

I've been coming here since 2013 and love this place. It's quiet, cozy and just an overall great spot for Indian fusion cuisine! 🌞(My favs are: Veggie combo, palak paneer, mushroom vindaloo, chana masala, mushroom and onion naan, and mango lassi.)

Always thought of trying this .... and when i tried i was cursing my stars. So bad was the food and service that i almost thought of not paying them.What they are charging for the kind of being provided is stupidity. The Pakora's were so oily that i had to use paper napkins to remove oil before eating them. Tandoori chicken was cold and under cooked.  Options are very less not sure why they call them buffet. Could not find any flavor. the only good thing was naan and water. Because that was the best combo i had from the available choices other best thing if you want to learn how to make food look good with food color.  I will not be going back even if they provide me with free food. This place is a disgrace to Indian food.
Slightly over priced but good food regardless.
Good Sunday Buffet!!
Can't beat that weekend lunch buffet. I recommend you utilize that special. Good quality. Beware of limited seating and limited parking.
Best Indian restaurant in town. Great menu and a Sunday brunch that is fantastic!
I am Indian and believe me the food we ordered was horrible.. No taste in the food but they had keep the prices very high..
My favorite Indian place since the other places I've been to have lost their way. The food is flavorful, spicy, and plentiful.
Their tandoori is fabulous. Portion sizes are generous. The food in general was really tasty. It's close to the L for your convenience.
Hands down the best chicken biryani in the city. My favorite place for Indian on or off Devon.

This place has the most terrible food in the name of desi food. Ordered a biryani ( very spicy) , and a mushroom curry. Please don't think that this is real authentic food. The food we ordered has no spice, or the masala that goes into a real biryani, curry. The rice was stale. Do yourself a favor and don't order from there. You're welcome!
Today was my first time trying Indian food,  and I loved it! Amazing service and delicious food.
Great place ..!  Butter chicken and breads are great but chicken biryani is little disappointing ..! Everything else are awesome
Best food
Great food! The buffet was reasonable...
Fine food, has all the dishes they have now at supermarkets meaning they are somewhat Americanized. Dishes dont come with rice.

One of the best Indian restaurants in Chicago! Steps from an el station and Lake Shore Drive, yet very quiet and pleasant. Two liquor stores located within walking distance (one next door!) if you forget to BYOB. The food is as authentic as you can get in the Midwest, and the prices are a steal! Highly, highly reccomend!

Wonderful, small, BYOB place. Really friendly staff complements some of the best Indian food in Chicago--we brought friends who have lived in India and both were more than satisfied. Also a great takeout option, but worth the trip with the BYOB and often comped dessert or apps :)
Wow! The food here is amazing. I had the Chicken Makhani with rice (which was a big portion) and Badami Kheer. Plus they had my order ready super fast.

Best lunch special in Edgewater! I order and pick up at least every other week. Very generous portions and prompt service. I am not an expert in Indian cuisine, so I cannot say it is the real deal, but it is good, palatable food.
Delicious and generous offerings
Very very fresh, very very good. Order at least once per week here.
Great food, good service, even with a complex set of food allergies.
Fantastic food, huge portions.
Grrat food, always a little quiet for my taste

The Chicken Tika Marsala keeps us coming back at least once a month. I have tried many of their other dishes and they are usually flavorful but nothing extremely impressive. The revamped menu has us interested in exploring the new options.
Veg biryani and samosa are so bad...rice quality is not good. Taste is so ordinary. ..
Delicious food, service was just a bit slow.
Best Indian food in chicago imho. Family run unit, almost always have the same server. Authentic quality with options that tone down some of the more wild authenticity. Good prices

I tried giving this place a chance multiple times. The food and waiting staff is very bad. I do not recommend this place to anyone. You can find much better Indian and Pakistani restaurants in Devon Street.
Absolutely amazing food. This has quickly become my favorite India restaurant. I recomand Chicken Makhani, amazing!
Had the brunch buffet and it was good.   The service was nice and they did a good job at making sure the little buffet area was kept stocked.  I'll be back.
Delicious food! I recommend coming into the restaurant to enjoy the food hot and fresh.
the food is good ....but this place is usually empty I don't know why
I order chicken with garlic sause and rise ... I picked it up and there was no chicken at all... I call them and they just made excuses for their mistake...

This is such a delicious restaurant. The food is always fantastic . Vegetable appetizer platter delicious; great naans, great palak paneer; great curries . New favorite eggplant and peas in spicy sauce. Oh and the best rice pudding. Staff is great. Portions are generous.

For delivery, they have a $20.00 minimum order and there dishes are overpriced based on the quality of the food.  The only decent dish they had on the menu was the chicken Tandoori but then again it's not easy to mess that up if you're an authentic Indian restaurant with a tandoor.  I also ordered a chicken Biryani which was a very small portion.  To make things worse, they had pieces of chopped tomatoes in a biryani! to likely cover up how bland the rice was.  Have never seen that any where lol.  Save your money and pick up some real Indian food from a place that will give you a good portion for your dollar and where the food will have some actual taste.  Shaan Foods is in the neighborhood and while it's not the greatest, it's still a no brainer over this place.
Awesome Indian food, at reasonable cost. We are Indians and it is our favorite restaurant in Chicago.
Everything was delicious and wait staff was competent.
Delicious and fresh food with friendly staff and management.

Indian food is one of my favorites. Tried this place one night over a year ago, when it was too crowded on Devon Ave. I'm so glad I did! Though I still go othere places as well, I keep coming back here. Small, but clean and the food is very good and fresh tasting. I'm heading over as I speak!!

If you've never had Chicken Tikka Masala then do yourself a favor and make sure your first time is here. Then all others in the city will fall short of how this restaurant makes it when you try exploring other Indian restaurants and compare how it's supposed to be made and taste.  This is the best place in the city for Chicken Tikka Masala bar none. The flavors, the creaminess is unlike anything and is well worth the initial trial. Give it a shot and tell me I am wrong. I bet you can't!  Make sure to order the regular naan bread with it and enjoy. You will not be sorry you took the chance.  I will not go as far as saying they are the best but this is the best version of this dish in town.
Plus: the food and byob. Negative: small and lacking in any kind of ambience.  Service was ok.
This is the best indian food place. Great service and healthy indian and delicious food. Highly recommended! They r also byob
Don't go in there! Food is maybe a little acceptable but service and hygiene are terribly bad.
This place is amazing.  The food is delicious.  PLUS it is a BYOB joint which saves you some cash.  I recommend ordering a combo platter -- plenty of food to share and a nice variety.
Great Food. The owner is sooo nice.  Cute place and convenient right of the red line... Bryn Mwar stop.

If you want delicious Indian food, at an incredibly reasonable price, served by genuinely nice people, this is the place for you. I love their lamb naan and the "non veg" appetizer will get you a taste of many different meats and is darn cheap.
we love the food here..the lunch special is awesome, the service we received from sumanth was great.  definitely recommended.
The inside is very small, even by Chicago standards. However, the food is very good and service has always been excellent.
